<!-- Q1 -->
<div class="q-panel active" id="qp-0">
  <div class="sat-layout">
    <div class="passage-panel">
      <div class="panel-label">Passage</div>
      <div class="passage-source">Adapted from a student essay on urban planning</div>
      <div class="passage-text">
        <span class="ln">1</span>Successful urban transit systems share several characteristics: they are financially sustainable, politically supported, and <span class="ul">the infrastructure is designed to be accessible to all riders regardless of income or ability</span>. Cities that ignore any one of these factors tend to build systems that serve commuters in wealthy neighborhoods while leaving lower-income residents underserved.<br><br>
        <span class="ln">6</span>The most effective transit investments, researchers argue, treat mobility as a public good rather than a commercial service — a distinction that shapes every decision from route planning to fare structure.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-panel-inner">
      <div class="q-label">Question 1 · Parallel Structure</div>
      <div class="q-text">Which choice most effectively corrects the underlined portion to maintain <strong>parallel structure</strong>?</div>
      <div class="opts" id="opts-0">
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'A')"><span class="opt-l">A</span>the infrastructure is designed to be accessible to all riders regardless of income or ability</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'B')"><span class="opt-l">B</span>they are accessible to all riders regardless of income or ability</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'C')"><span class="opt-l">C</span>accessibility for all riders regardless of income or ability</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'D')"><span class="opt-l">D</span>designing the infrastructure to be accessible to all riders regardless of income or ability</div>
      </div>
      <div class="q-actions">
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-0-ok"><strong>Correct!</strong> The list establishes a clear pattern: "they are financially sustainable, [they are] politically supported, and [they are] ___." Each item is an adjective predicate following "they are." The third item must also be an adjective predicate: "they are accessible to all riders." Option B correctly completes the parallel: "financially sustainable, politically supported, and accessible." Option A introduces a new subject ("the infrastructure") breaking the "they are" structure. Option C shifts to a noun phrase. Option D uses a gerund phrase that doesn't fit the predicate adjective pattern.</div>
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-0-fail"><strong>Not quite.</strong> Identify the pattern: "they are financially sustainable, [they are] politically supported, and [they are] ___." The first two items are adjective predicates following "they are." Which option completes the third item with another adjective predicate in the same form?</div>
        <button class="btn-check" id="btn-0" onclick="check(0,'B')" disabled>Check answer</button>
      </div>
    </div>
