<!-- Q2 -->
<div class="q-panel" id="qp-1">
  <div class="sat-layout">
    <div class="passage-panel">
      <div class="panel-label">Passage</div>
      <div class="passage-source">Adapted from a scientific article on ocean plastic pollution</div>
      <div class="passage-text">
        <span class="ln">1</span>Marine biologists studying the effects of plastic pollution have found that microplastics not only accumulate in the tissues of fish and marine mammals <span class="ul">but they also are entering the human food chain through seafood consumption</span>. The implications for public health are still being studied, but preliminary data suggest a correlation between high seafood consumption and elevated levels of microplastic particles in blood and tissue samples.<br><br>
        <span class="ln">7</span>Researchers call for improved waste management systems, stricter regulations on single-use plastics, and expanded monitoring of microplastic levels in food supplies.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-panel-inner">
      <div class="q-label">Question 2 · Parallel Structure</div>
      <div class="q-text">Which choice corrects the underlined portion to maintain <strong>parallel structure</strong> with the paired conjunction?</div>
      <div class="opts" id="opts-1">
