        <div class="feedback" id="fb-1-fail"><strong>Not quite.</strong> With "not only…but also," the grammatical form must match on both sides. What follows "not only"? "accumulate" — a bare infinitive (base form verb). What must follow "but also"? A bare infinitive in the same form. Which option uses a bare infinitive to match "accumulate"?</div>
